Package org.sbml.squeezer

This is the core of SBMLsqueezer as it contains the central classes for reaction type analysis, kineticl law generation and some specialized exceptions.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    OptionsGeneral
    This is a list of possible command line options and configuration of SBMLsqueezer.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConsistencyReportBuilder
    This class takes a list of SBMLExceptions as input and generates a nicely formatted human-readable report from it - based on a given FormatBuilder.
    KineticLawGenerator
    This class identifies and generates the missing kinetic laws for a the selected model in the given plug-in.
    ParameterFactory
    This class has many factory methods for the creation of parameters to be used in varous kinetic equations for a specific model.
    ReactionType
    The purpose of this class is to analyze a reaction object for several properties, such as the number of reactants and products, the types of modifiers and their number, if the stoichiometries are always integer numbers or real valued and much more.
    SBMLsqueezer<T>
    The main program of SBMLsqueezer.
    SubmodelController
    This class is responsible for miniModel creation and the synchronisation with the main Model
    UnitFactory
    A factory class that creates frequently used instances of Unit and UnitDefinition if these are not yet present in a Model.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    UnitConsistencyType
    This is an enumeration of the two possible ways of how to ensure consistent units within an SBML model; reacting species might either be given in molecule counts (UnitConsistencyType.amount) or their UnitConsistencyType.concentration.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ModificationException
    An exception that can be raised if a wront type of modification is assigned to a reaction; it is a special kind of a RateLawNotApplicableException.
    RateLawNotApplicableException
    An exception to be thrown if the selected kinetics is not applicable to the given reaction.
